
A) Create a ros2 workspace and place the exercise files in it

1.
    Ho creato una directory ros2/src e ho inserito la cartella EX1 all'interno
2.
    Ho apero un terminale in /ros2_ws e ho seguito questi comandi:
        - source /opt/ros/humble/setup.bash
        - colcon build
            OUTPUT->  Starting >>> sysmonitor_interfaces
                      Finished <<< sysmonitor_interfaces [4.18s]

                      Summary: 1 package finished [4.59s]
3.
    Ho verificato che l'operazione fosse andata a buon fine controllando le directory create con:
        - ls
            OUTPUT->  build  install  log  src




B) Determine how many topics are in the bag

1.
    Ho aperto un altro terminale in /ros2_ws eseguendo:
        - source install/setup.bash

2.
    Ho eseguito i comandi:
        - sudo apt install ros-humble-rosbag2-storage-mcap
        - cd src/EX1/rosbag2_2024_11_22-00_32_31
        - ros2 bag info rosbag2_2024_11_22-00_32_31_0.mcap
            OUTPUT->    closing.

                        Files:             rosbag2_2024_11_22-00_32_31_0.mcap
                        Bag size:          68.7 MiB
                        Storage id:        mcap
                        Duration:          10.626805833s
                        Start:             Nov 22 2024 00:32:31.698013076 (1732231951.698013076)
                        End:               Nov 22 2024 00:32:42.324818909 (1732231962.324818909)
                        Messages:          1246
                        Topic information:  Topic: /imu/acceleration | Type: geometry_msgs/msg/Vector3Stamped | Count: 0 | Serialization Format: cdr
                                            Topic: /imu/angular_velocity | Type: geometry_msgs/msg/Vector3Stamped | Count: 0 | Serialization Format: cdr
                                            Topic: /imu/data | Type: sensor_msgs/msg/Imu | Count: 916 | Serialization Format: cdr
                                            Topic: /zed2i/zed_node/left_gray/image_rect_gray | Type: sensor_msgs/msg/Image | Count: 311 | Serialization Format: cdr
                                            Topic: /system_info | Type: sysmonitor_interfaces/msg/Sysmon | Count: 19 | Serialization Format: cdr
3.
    RISPOSTA: abbiamo 5 topics elencati nell'output precedente




C) Determine the Hz of the topic image

1.
    Dalle info ricavate dal punto C) abbiamo:
        a) Duration: 10.626805833s
        b) Topic: /zed2i/zed_node/left_gray/image_rect_gray | Type: sensor_msgs/msg/Image | Count: 311

2.
    Calcolo della frequenza del topic Image:
        f=Count/Duration=311/10.626805833

3.
    RISPOSTA: f=29,265 Hz




D) Determine the Hz of the topic system

1.
    Dalle info ricavate dal punto C) abbiamo:
        a) Duration: 10.626805833s
        b) Topic: /system_info | Type: sysmonitor_interfaces/msg/Sysmon | Count: 19

2.
    Calcolo della frequenza del topic Image:
        f=Count/Duration=19/10.626805833

3.
    RISPOSTA: f=1,787 Hz




E) Determine what does the topic system return

1.
    Dalle info ricavate dal punto C) abbiamo:
        Topic: /system_info | Type: sysmonitor_interfaces/msg/Sysmon

2.
    Per capire di che tipo di messaggio si tratta ho usato il comando:
        - ros2 interface show sysmonitor_interfaces/msg/Sysmon
            OUTPUT->    float64 cpu_usage
                        float64 cpu_temp
                        float64 ram_usage
                        float64 gpu_usage
                        float64 gpu_temp
                        float64 gpuram_usage

3.
    RISPOSTA: il topic ritorna un messaggio di tipo:
    Sysmon{
        float64 cpu_usage
        float64 cpu_temp
        float64 ram_usage
        float64 gpu_usage
        float64 gpu_temp
        float64 gpuram_usage
    }

